The two lost kittens who shut down a portion of the New York City subway system Thursday after wandering onto the tracks should count their lucky stars that Joe Lhota is not the mayor yet.

The former chairman of the Metropolitan Transit Authority and mayoral hopeful said he wouldn’t have stopped the subway as the kittens dubbed Arthur and August scrambled along the tracks.

A spokesman for Lhota told the New York Post on Friday that the candidate doesn’t think stopping service for wayward cats is appropriate.

